    </p>

    <h3>Information We Collect</h3>

    <p><strong>Camera Access</strong><br>
      Used only to scan food labels and ingredient lists.
      Images are processed locally or temporarily and are not permanently stored.
    </p>

    <p><strong>App Usage Data</strong><br>
      Non-personal analytics such as feature usage, crashes, and performance data.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Subscription Information</strong><br>
      Managed by Apple In-App Purchases.
      We do not store payment or billing details.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Device Information</strong><br>
      Device type, operating system version, and app version.
    </p>

    <h3>What We Do Not Collect</h3>
    <p>
      We do not collect sensitive personal data, medical records, precise location data,
      or biometric information.
      We do not sell personal data.
    </p>

    <h3>How Information Is Used</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide and improve app functionality</li>
      <li>Operate subscriptions and premium features</li>
      <li>Fix bugs and improve performance</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
    <p>
      The app may use services such as Apple In-App Purchases, analytics providers
      (e.g., Apple or Firebase), and subscription services (e.g., Superwall).
      These services only receive data required to perform their functions.
    </p>

    <h3>Data Retention</h3>
    <p>
      Data is retained only as long as necessary.
      Users may request deletion of non-purchase data by contacting support.
    </p>

    <h3>User Rights</h3>
    <p>
      You may request access, updates, or deletion of your data by emailing support.
